        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 4:23AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 422 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms from
northeastern Haskell County south into northeastern Jones County,
moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Haskell, Stamford, Albany, Throckmorton, Lueders, Woodson, Weinert,
Irby, Paint Creek, Nugent, Elbert, Avoca, Lake Stamford Marina,
Millers Creek Reservoir, Fort Griffin, Funston, and Lusk.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
